{"id":"10930","name":"Seek Telegram Message by ID","tagline":"Open Telegram message by specified channel(or)group/messageID.","icon":"ios15 c3031607807 g59836","latest":"31518","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<p><img alt=\"TelegramShortcuts\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/43663476/151065307-88e3eaa0-ce93-4a89-b91c-c50fb649cc4d.png\"></p>\n<p>This shortcut constructs the standard URL to a specific Telegram message in a public channel or group via two <a href=\"https://www.matthewcassinelli.com/actions/ask-for-input/\">Ask for Input</a> actions: \n1. The @ name of the subject channel/group (without the @.) Ex: <code>extratone</code>\n2. The numeric message ID of the subject message. Ex: <code>9911</code>\nThe two are then combined: <code>https://t.me/extratone/9911</code>, which is copied to the clipboard and opened in Telegram via an <a href=\"https://www.matthewcassinelli.com/actions/open-urls\">Open URLs</a> action.</p>\n<p>Upon installation, youâ€™ll be prompted to set default values for both, but neither are required.</p>\n<h2>More Siri Shortcuts for Telegram (and a few other configurables) can be found on my \"<a href=\"https://bilge.world/telegram-extras\"><strong>Telegram Extras</strong></a>\" blog post.</h2>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://davidblue.wtf/db.vcf\">Contact Card</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://t.me/extratone\">Telegram</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"mailto:davidblue@extratone.com\">Email</a> </li>\n<li><a href=\"https://twitter.com/NeoYokel\">Twitter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://mastodon.social/@DavidBlue\">Mastodon</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://discord.gg/0b9KQUKP858b0iZF\">Discord</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://raindrop.io/davidblue/social-directory-21059174\">-Everywhere-</a>...</li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0 - Jan. 26, 2022, 12:13 a.m.</strong></p>"}